---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	locale="en"
	title="AirTM">
	<section class="project-hero">
		<video autoplay loop muted playsinline class="hero-bg" style="object-fit:cover">
			<source src="/projects/airtm/AIRtM1.mp4" type="video/mp4"/>
		</video>
		<div class="hero-overlay" style="backdrop-filter:blur(15px);-webkit-backdrop-filter:blur(15px)"></div>
		<div class="container">
			<div class="hero-content">
				<a
					href="/#results"
					class="back-link"
					><svg
						width="20"
						height="20"
						viewBox="0 0 20 20"
						fill="none"
						><path
							d="M15 5L5 10L15 15"
							stroke="currentColor"
							stroke-width="1.5"
							stroke-linecap="round"
							stroke-linejoin="round"
						></path></svg
					>Back</a
				>
				<h1 class="project-title">AirTM</h1>
				<p class="project-tagline">Proposal within the recruitment process</p>
				<p class="project-context">Finance — Global / LATAM</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="project-section">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="section-label-text"><i>01</i> Problem</span>
			<p class="project-body">
				This was a test proposal within the recruitment process to enter the
				AIRTM company. Airtm is the easiest way to move money abroad. It helps
				people send and receive money, no matter what type of currency they use.
				It's a dollar tool that helps you send and receive money and fight
				hyperinflation by exchanging your local currency for dollars. The
				interface had visual inconsistencies, complex navigation, and lacked
				hierarchy for key financial functions. We work with developing countries
				to help them get better financial services.
			</p>
			<div class="project-tags">
				<span class="">UI/UX</span><span class="tag">Strategy</span><span
					class="tag">Branding & Identity</span
				><span class="tag">Web Design & Development</span><span class="tag"
					>Illustration</span
				><span class="tag">Video Editing</span>
			</div>

			<img
				src="/projects/airtm/1fdd1a113587893.602b559f49d24-1.gif"
				alt="AirTM UI"
				class="img-fluid"
				style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:2rem"
			/>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="project-section-alt">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="section-label-text"><i>02</i> System & Approach</span>
			<p class="project-body">
				Starting with research and user acceptance testing, we documented areas
				of opportunity divided into three clearly defined objectives:
			</p>
			<ol class="project-list">
				<li>
					<strong>Consistent design system</strong> — implement a unified visual foundation.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Side menu</strong> — include quick and accessible navigation.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Accessibility features</strong> — incorporate features for all users.
				</li>
			</ol>
			<p class="project-body">
				After analyzing the user journey map, secondary actions were moved from
				the menu to dropdowns in the top bar. The new debit card feature was
				added and visual feedback of the user's current position was improved.
			</p>
			<p class="project-body">
				A new layout was created to display the same amount of vital information
				while making room for additional essential features such as quick
				actions and search. The login and sign-in screens were redesigned
				completely to create a more welcoming and intuitive experience.
			</p>
			<div class="project-process">
				<strong>Process:</strong> discover → hypothesize → prototype
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="project-gallery">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="section-label-text mb-4">Corporate color palette</span>
			<div class="project-colors">
				<div
					class="row"
					style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:2rem">
					{
						[
							{ bg: '#77CCFF', c: 'black' },
							{ bg: '#0088FF', c: 'white' },
							{ bg: '#002233', c: 'white' },
							{ bg: '#00BB55', c: 'white' },
							{ bg: '#FFCC00', c: 'black' },
							{ bg: '#F0F1F2', c: 'black' },
						].map((c) => (
							<div
								class="ColorSample p-3"
								style={`background:${c.bg};min-width:120px;flex:1`}>
								<p
									style={`color:${c.c};margin:0;font-family:monospace;font-size:0.8rem`}>
									{c.bg}
								</p>
							</div>
						))
					}
				</div>
			</div>

			<img
				src="/projects/airtm/ui.gif"
				alt="AirTM UI flows"
				class="img-fluid"
				style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:2rem"
			/>
			<img
				src="/projects/airtm/AirTm-UI-UX-Designer.jpg"
				alt="AirTM UX design"
				class="img-fluid"
				style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:2rem"
			/>
			<img
				src="/projects/airtm/cardDesign.jpg"
				alt="AirTM card design"
				class="img-fluid"
				style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:2rem"
			/>
			<video
				controls
				class="img-fluid"
				style="width:100%;border-radius:12px">
				<source
					src="/projects/airtm/AIRtM1.mp4"
					type="video/mp4"
				/>
			</video>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="project-result">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="result-box">
				<h2>Result</h2><p>
					The designs were not implemented, however several proposals were made
					to improve the usability of the platform. Clear foundations for design
					system, navigation, and accessibility were laid for future product
					iterations.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="project-section">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="section-label-text"><i>03</i> Learnings</span><p
				class="project-body">
				Financial interfaces demand absolute clarity. Every element must convey
				security and trust. The recruitment process as a test case demonstrated
				that even unimplemented proposals generate value when they document a
				structured approach to research and design.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<style>
		.tag {
			color: black;
		}
		.project-hero {
			background-image: url();
		}
	</style>
</BaseLayout>
